Almost half of dog owners did not know ticks can transmit deadly diseases to humans and other dogs . 
  54 per cent did not realise Lyme disease affects their pets as well as themselves . 
  Concerned vets across the UK are urging the public to get their dogs checked out for ticks . 
  Ticks can spread potentially fatal diseases - such as Lyme disease - to humans . 
  Knowledge about Lyme disease is increasing . 
 